
### £ man_1_simple_shell

Save this file as **man_1_simple_shell** (no extension):

```man
.TH simple_shell 1 "October 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh
.br
Reads commands from standard input and executes them.
.SH DESCRIPTION
The simple_shell is a minimal UNIX shell written in C. It reads commands from the user, parses them, and executes them either as built-in commands or by forking a process and executing binaries found in the directories listed in the PATH environment variable.

The shell operates in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
.EX
$ ./hsh
$ ls -l
$ pwd
$ exit
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.EX
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
.EE

.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Lamis Fahad Aljabli and Raneem Tarik Alsaqat for Holberton School.
